1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,074
Subtitles downloaded from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:01:47,807 --> 00:01:51,880
My legs, my poor legs! Why
are they striking?

3
00:01:51,927 --> 00:01:55,920
- Because you don't have a social
conscience. - And you? - I do.

4
00:01:55,967 --> 00:01:58,800
- Don't your legs hurt ?
- Sure they do!

5
00:02:26,887 --> 00:02:30,846
- Good evening. The elevator
is broken. - It's hardly a surprise!

6
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:53,746
- How are you, Michel ?
Is he in ? - Yes, Mrs.

7
00:02:53,787 --> 00:02:57,905
- Is everything all right ? - I believe so.
- I'll have a look at the dinner table.

8
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:06,977
Yes, very well.
Take this, please.

9
00:03:12,507 --> 00:03:14,657
- Did you do your homeworks ?
- Yes.

10
00:03:14,707 --> 00:03:17,665
What's going on ? Come here !

11
00:03:17,707 --> 00:03:21,746
- Listen, I need to talk to you.
- Yes, Michel.

12
00:03:22,787 --> 00:03:26,223
- Hello, George ! 
- What happened to you? It's so late !

13
00:03:26,267 --> 00:03:30,499
Oh, yes, I know ! Blame the strike !

14
00:03:30,547 --> 00:03:33,345
There was a big mess in Largo Argentina

15
00:03:33,387 --> 00:03:35,901
They rerouted me through
an endless series of alleys !

16
00:03:35,947 --> 00:03:39,986
I wanted to tell you that I had
to invite aunt Margareth and her son.

17
00:03:40,027 --> 00:03:43,656
- Tonight ? - She called me
once you went out.

18
00:03:43,707 --> 00:03:46,665
She'll be in Rome just for
three days, I didn't know what to tell her.

19
00:03:46,707 --> 00:03:48,698
There won't have been
another occasion.

20
00:03:48,747 --> 00:03:51,944
You're really sympathetic
towards Andrea and his ideas.

21
00:03:51,987 --> 00:03:54,865
Maybe in front of his mother
he'll avoid to raise the crowd.

22
00:03:54,907 --> 00:03:57,705
At least you, try to be fast,
I need to change my dress!

23
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:09,977
- Tell me: what did you do
all day long - Nothing.

24
00:04:10,027 --> 00:04:13,542
What do you mean, nothing ?
It's ringing, call Cesira.

25
00:04:19,027 --> 00:04:22,736
- Can you listen to me, now ?
- Sure, but be fast.

26
00:04:22,787 --> 00:04:24,778
Come in!

27
00:04:24,827 --> 00:04:28,297
Cesira, I don't know if
I already told you, in the kitchen...

28
00:04:28,347 --> 00:04:30,986
..to cook something light
for Mrs. Casati.

29
00:04:31,027 --> 00:04:33,825
Mafalda boiled some of the fish
she bought for the child.

30
00:04:33,867 --> 00:04:36,745
Fine. Thanks. You may go, Cesira.

31
00:04:36,787 --> 00:04:38,664
Mom, can you listen to me ?

32
00:04:38,707 --> 00:04:43,019
Go ahead. But turn around,
I need to undress.

33
00:04:49,387 --> 00:04:53,699
- So, what did you want to say ?
- I'm not gonna say anything anymore.

34
00:04:53,747 --> 00:04:56,102
You really want to make me
mad. Come on, what's up ?

35
00:04:56,147 --> 00:04:58,183
I've been alone all day
in this house.

36
00:04:58,227 --> 00:05:01,822
-Didn't your support teacher
come ? - No, not even today.

37
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:04,586
Probably because of the strike...
There was no public transportation.

38
00:05:04,627 --> 00:05:07,699
Even last week he missed
two days in a row.

39
00:05:07,747 --> 00:05:09,658
You knew he wasn't feeling fine.

40
00:05:09,707 --> 00:05:13,700
I'll call him tomorrow and
we'll send a car for him. Happy ?

41
00:05:13,747 --> 00:05:17,183
- No.
- So, what is it that you want ?

42
00:05:17,227 --> 00:05:22,142
I don't like my support teacher,
he talks a lot and he's always too close.

43
00:05:22,187 --> 00:05:24,940
He sweats, he laughs... I don't like him.

44
00:05:24,987 --> 00:05:27,820
You wish you could be with
your nanny again, don't you?

45
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:31,064
But you are a man now,
you need a man like you.

46
00:05:31,107 --> 00:05:33,302
Oh, God, that Cesira !

47
00:05:33,347 --> 00:05:38,944
Cesira, get my white dress and
my shoes ready ! Quick !

48
00:05:38,987 --> 00:05:43,105
- I'm sorry, with all this confusion...
- Good evening. - Good evening, Mrs.

49
00:05:43,147 --> 00:05:46,105
- Is the champagne cooling in the fridge?
- Yes, yes.

50
00:05:47,907 --> 00:05:50,546
- Go get it. - Sure.

51
00:05:50,587 --> 00:05:52,782
George, go ahead in the meanwhile.

52
00:05:53,587 --> 00:05:55,418
I'll be ready soon.

53
00:05:57,667 --> 00:06:00,465
- Good night, Michel.
- Bye.

54
00:06:01,627 --> 00:06:04,903
- Where were we ?
- Where have you been today ?

55
00:06:04,947 --> 00:06:09,338
I've been... What do you mean,
''Where have you been today'' ?

56
00:06:09,387 --> 00:06:11,503
Should you ask such questions
to your mother ?

57
00:06:11,547 --> 00:06:14,459
We really need
to talk:...

58
00:06:14,507 --> 00:06:17,340
..It's completely unproper for a guy
like you, who owns everything...

59
00:06:17,387 --> 00:06:20,459
..to be always nervous and unhappy,
like a crybaby.

60
00:06:20,507 --> 00:06:23,943
- We'll talk about it later.
- Where's mom ? - Here.

61
00:06:23,987 --> 00:06:27,502
- Hello. Quick, the Orange are
already here. - I'm coming.

62
00:06:27,547 --> 00:06:31,381
I have to tell you what
happened at the Antonelli's place !

63
00:06:31,427 --> 00:06:34,146
You look so good !

64
00:06:52,507 --> 00:06:55,499
Good evening ! How are you ?

65
00:06:55,547 --> 00:06:58,107
- Dear ! - Hello !
- Good evening ! - Good evening !

66
00:06:58,147 --> 00:07:00,058
Look what Richard brought
for Michel !

67
00:07:00,107 --> 00:07:03,941
Thanks ! He'll be very happy !
So kind of you, Richard.

68
00:07:03,987 --> 00:07:07,184
- Here's aunt Margareth.
- Aunt Margareth ! How are you?

69
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:09,457
- Good evening, Irene.
- Good evening. - Good evening.

70
00:07:09,507 --> 00:07:13,022
- She's better, don't you think ?
- Yes. She lost a little weight, maybe.

71
00:07:13,067 --> 00:07:16,503
- Let me introduce you to Mrs. Orange.
- How do you do.

72
00:07:16,547 --> 00:07:18,458
- Mister Chandler.
- How do you do.

73
00:07:18,507 --> 00:07:20,816
Mister Orange.
Do you remember Luciana ?

74
00:07:20,867 --> 00:07:22,937
Mrs. Casati
and her son Andrea.

75
00:07:22,987 --> 00:07:24,978
Come sit down, aunt Margareth.

76
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:29,896
- Let's show Michel his toy.
Call him, he has yet to make it to bed. - Yes.

77
00:07:29,947 --> 00:07:32,780
- What do we want to drink?
You already have something. - Yes, thanks.

78
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:34,738
Aunt Margareth, care for a drink ?

79
00:07:34,787 --> 00:07:37,540
No, thanks.
Or maybe a vermouth, a little bit.

80
00:07:37,587 --> 00:07:41,660
- A vermouth. Andrea ?
- Nothing, thanks. - Nothing ?

81
00:07:41,707 --> 00:07:45,905
- Here. And me ? Luciana, what do you want?
- A dry Martini.

82
00:07:45,947 --> 00:07:49,701
Good idea, I'll go along with it !
Ah, Michel !

83
00:07:49,747 --> 00:07:53,899
Look what Mister Orange brought
you ! Say hello to aunt Margareth.

84
00:07:53,947 --> 00:07:57,826
You grow up so fast !
Last year you were like this !

85
00:07:57,867 --> 00:08:01,064
But you're a bit pale, my dear.
Maybe too much study, eh ?

86
00:08:01,107 --> 00:08:04,702
- Yes, it's true. He looks tired.
- Michel ?

87
00:08:05,507 --> 00:08:09,102
- Did you say hello to Mrs. Orange ?
- Hello, dear. - Good evening.

88
00:08:09,147 --> 00:08:14,267
- Do you remember your cousin Andrea ?
- How are you, Michel ? - Fine.

89
00:08:14,307 --> 00:08:16,901
Say thanks to Mr.Orange.

90
00:08:17,547 --> 00:08:19,299
Thanks.

91
00:08:20,187 --> 00:08:23,463
Ins't it wonderful ?
Are you happy ?

92
00:08:23,507 --> 00:08:26,863
Say goodbye to everybody, now.
Go and be nice, ok ?

93
00:08:26,907 --> 00:08:28,943
- Did you all get served ?
- yes, thanks.

94
00:08:28,987 --> 00:08:30,978
How long are you staying,
Aunt Margareth ?

95
00:08:31,027 --> 00:08:33,495
Up until my husband will
be done with his businesses.

96
00:08:33,547 --> 00:08:37,256
- Do we want to try the train ?
- Why not ? - Let's go.

97
00:08:46,587 --> 00:08:50,705
What are you doing, there ?
Do you want to have fun all on your own ?

98
00:08:50,747 --> 00:08:52,977
Do we want to go and see ?

99
00:09:02,547 --> 00:09:04,742
- Let's stop it.
- Your glass.

100
00:09:04,787 --> 00:09:11,306
- Thanks. Now, rear motion !
- It's really funny ! It seems true !

101
00:09:11,987 --> 00:09:15,775
- Mrs., the meal is served.
- Lunch is ready !

102
00:09:16,427 --> 00:09:18,224
Do we want to go ?

103
00:09:19,947 --> 00:09:23,337
- It's funny even for adults.
- Do you want to sit down ?

104
00:09:23,387 --> 00:09:27,141
Aunt Margareth, Richard:
are you hungry ?

105
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:32,706
You're here, Richard here,...

106
00:09:32,747 --> 00:09:38,379
..Andrea to my left,
then George...

107
00:09:38,427 --> 00:09:41,942
No, I'm wrong,
aunt Margareth will sit right there.

108
00:09:41,987 --> 00:09:46,060
Richard to her right
and George there. Let's sit down.

109
00:09:46,107 --> 00:09:49,144
Sorry, I'm always wrong.

110
00:09:49,187 --> 00:09:51,257
Aunt Margareth.

111
00:09:51,307 --> 00:09:54,026
These things make me confused,
I always make a mess.

112
00:09:57,347 --> 00:10:00,862
- How long have you been in Italy?
- Many years.

113
00:10:00,907 --> 00:10:04,502
I studied in Florence
with my sister, George's mother.

114
00:10:04,547 --> 00:10:07,425
Then I married an italian,
Vladimiro Casati.

115
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:09,822
- Does your son work in Italy ?
- Yes, here in Rome.

116
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:12,700
- What does he do ?
- He's a journalist.

117
00:10:12,747 --> 00:10:18,105
A journalist ? Then he might be able to
tell us if there will be peace or war.

118
00:10:18,147 --> 00:10:20,183
I'd say peace.

119
00:10:20,227 --> 00:10:24,505
You're very optimistic, bless you.
I'll believe there will be war.

120
00:10:24,547 --> 00:10:28,017
- I hope for peace.
- I can't see how. Am I wrong ?

121
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:30,865
I have some particular ideas
in this regard.

122
00:10:30,907 --> 00:10:33,865
You're so keen on politics !
I don't get any of it !

123
00:10:33,907 --> 00:10:36,785
- Have you been to that horse contest ?
- Excuse me a sec.

124
00:10:36,827 --> 00:10:39,466
I would like you to tell me
why you are so optimistic.

125
00:10:39,507 --> 00:10:42,544
Because there's so many of us, in the world,
wishing for peace, my lady.

126
00:10:42,587 --> 00:10:45,579
Yvonne dear, maybe it's
better to change topic.

127
00:10:45,627 --> 00:10:47,777
Andrea is a leftie.

128
00:10:47,827 --> 00:10:51,900
- A socialist ?
- Worst than that, I'm afraid.

129
00:10:51,947 --> 00:10:55,542
Mrs., Michel told me to
call you. You'd better go.

130
00:10:58,147 --> 00:11:03,426
Excuse me, I'm going to
check on my son.

131
00:11:03,467 --> 00:11:06,584
To peace ! Cin cin !

132
00:11:15,707 --> 00:11:19,382
I solved many problems,
but this boy is an enigma.

133
00:11:19,427 --> 00:11:24,626
- What's up ? - I feel sick.
- Your stomach ? - yes, it hurts.

134
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:30,424
- Where does it hurt ? - All over.
- Here ? - Ouch ! - Here ? - Oh...

135
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:35,495
You're fine. Stay put, do not put
on the same show.

136
00:11:35,547 --> 00:11:39,620
- You're not a child anymore!
- I can't sleep. Stay with me for a while.

137
00:11:39,667 --> 00:11:42,818
I can't, we have guests.
Don't be silly, sleep now.

138
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:46,098
- Go away, I dont want to see you !
- Be nice !

139
00:11:46,147 --> 00:11:49,344
Aren't you ashamed ? You're naked !

140
00:11:56,907 --> 00:12:00,866
It's Michel again.

141
00:12:00,907 --> 00:12:04,695
Go to see if you can calm him.

142
00:12:09,027 --> 00:12:13,942
Cesira, tell him I said to be
nice and sleep.

143
00:12:13,987 --> 00:12:16,103
He's so nervous since a while...

144
00:12:16,147 --> 00:12:19,583
He had a nanny since he was born,
up until six months ago,...

145
00:12:19,627 --> 00:12:22,699
..then George decided to send her away:
maybe that's why he's so nervous.

146
00:12:22,747 --> 00:12:25,500
Boys that age would better
stay in a college.

147
00:12:25,547 --> 00:12:28,220
Michel is not like the other
boys, he's very sensible.

148
00:12:28,267 --> 00:12:31,464
Even for me it's difficult to
understand him. And I'm his mother.

149
00:12:31,507 --> 00:12:34,544
Just imagine how little
would others understand.

150
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:38,136
Nowadays educational systems
are very, very forward.

151
00:12:38,187 --> 00:12:41,145
It's true. Our Switzerland
colleges are wonderful.

152
00:12:41,187 --> 00:12:44,384
I think it's isolation that
makes children perky.

153
00:12:44,427 --> 00:12:46,418
That's my thought, too.

154
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:50,221
Look at Chandler's son: he's in
a college and perfectly ok.

155
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:52,303
Really.

156
00:12:52,347 --> 00:12:54,338
He's just one year
older than Michel and a while ago...

157
00:12:54,387 --> 00:12:57,982
..he flew in from Boston all on his own
and he left to go back nice and smooth.

158
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:01,622
Over the Atlantic on a plane ?
Weren't you scared to send him ?

159
00:13:01,667 --> 00:13:03,703
Not really !
He had a lot of fun.

160
00:13:03,747 --> 00:13:05,977
I understand.

161
00:13:06,027 --> 00:13:08,746
Keep in mind that while George was
fighting at the front, during the war...

162
00:13:08,787 --> 00:13:13,338
..Michel and I stayed in England
during the bombings.

163
00:13:13,387 --> 00:13:15,537
Lady, the child hurt himself !

164
00:13:15,587 --> 00:13:17,896
- Where ?
- Down the stairs !

165
00:13:25,147 --> 00:13:28,696
- Michel !
- Don't worry, it's nothing serious !

166
00:13:28,747 --> 00:13:32,581
- Michel ! But...
- Easy, lady.

167
00:13:32,627 --> 00:13:35,619
Cesira, give me the car keys !

168
00:13:42,067 --> 00:13:44,820
The keys are in the fur coat
pockets !

169
00:14:06,787 --> 00:14:08,823
Ahead ! Keep going ahead !

170
00:14:10,987 --> 00:14:13,979
Santo Spirito Hospital,
towards Castel Sant'Angelo !

171
00:14:42,547 --> 00:14:45,698
Nothing serious:
his femur is lightly fractured.

172
00:14:45,747 --> 00:14:48,898
He threw up, but I guess we
can exclude cerebral commotion.

173
00:14:48,947 --> 00:14:53,145
He's now in the operating room.
He's sedated. They're almost done.

174
00:14:53,187 --> 00:14:56,862
I would like Alessandrini to visit him.
I'll try calling him again.

175
00:14:56,907 --> 00:15:00,297
He would like to make a phone call.
Can you escort him ?

176
00:15:06,227 --> 00:15:09,139
Poor Irene !

177
00:15:14,707 --> 00:15:16,618
Michel !

178
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:24,579
- Doctor...
- Everything is fine, Mrs.

179
00:15:31,887 --> 00:15:37,245
Don't cry, everything will be fine.

180
00:15:48,687 --> 00:15:53,124
I'm sorry.
These things happen to childrens.

181
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:57,001
- Call the doctor on duty.
- His femur is fractured.

182
00:15:57,047 --> 00:16:01,086
Recovery will be long,
but you shouldn't worry.

183
00:16:02,487 --> 00:16:04,955
- Cassiani.
- Nice to meet you. No complications?

184
00:16:05,007 --> 00:16:08,477
- Just a light shock state - Ah...
- Can't we bring him home ?

185
00:16:08,527 --> 00:16:10,518
Not yet,
he's still sedated.

186
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:13,035
Can't we at least find a
room to rent ?

187
00:16:13,087 --> 00:16:15,601
It's impossible for tonight,
maybe tomorrow.

188
00:16:15,647 --> 00:16:17,842
But tomorrow
you might bring him home.

189
00:16:25,687 --> 00:16:27,803
When did they inject him ?

190
00:16:27,847 --> 00:16:32,398
I've just put him in bed.
Can you see how calm he is ?

191
00:16:32,447 --> 00:16:36,838
- Morphine to so young a child...
Isn't it dangerous ? - No.

192
00:16:36,887 --> 00:16:40,721
And it's not morphine, it's Pantopon,
a weaker sedative.

193
00:16:40,767 --> 00:16:46,046
- Wouldn't it hurt him ?
- No. Don't worry.

194
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:53,355
Fractures like that are very painful
during the first days.

195
00:16:53,407 --> 00:16:56,001
Yes, I understand.

196
00:16:57,287 --> 00:17:01,678
Lady...
Mr. Casati is here.

197
00:17:01,727 --> 00:17:04,685
Let him through.
I'm outside.

198
00:17:05,827 --> 00:17:10,025
- Please, sit down.
- Good morning, Andrea.

199
00:17:10,067 --> 00:17:12,820
- How are you ?
- Not that fine.

200
00:17:12,867 --> 00:17:16,985
- It might have gone worst.
- I'm very confused.

201
00:17:17,027 --> 00:17:21,225
Try not to think about it.

202
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:26,660
- I just came to say goodbye. I'm going
away for a few days - Yes ?

203
00:17:26,707 --> 00:17:31,383
- Is there something I might
do for you? - No, thanks.

204
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:39,024
I don't know if it's a good idea,
to be telling you this.

205
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:42,821
The hospital doctor, which is a
friend of mine, told me that...

206
00:17:42,867 --> 00:17:49,784
..he had the impression that
the fall was voluntary.

207
00:17:49,827 --> 00:17:54,218
- What do you mean with "voluntary" ?
- Nothing. Stay calm, Irene.

208
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:57,179
Apparently Michel said some
things while still sedated...

209
00:17:57,227 --> 00:18:00,060
..and so my friend thought he
needed to let you know.

210
00:18:00,107 --> 00:18:03,224
He told me so that I could find
the most proper way to...

211
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:06,957
It's absurd !

212
00:18:07,007 --> 00:18:10,966
Maybe, but my friend said
that sensible children...

213
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:15,523
..are capable of everything,
even of such extreme gestures.

214
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:19,162
- It's impossible ! Andrea !
- Stay calm, at times children are...

215
00:18:19,207 --> 00:18:22,517
Mom ? Mom?

216
00:18:23,527 --> 00:18:26,599
I'm coming. Excuse me a sec.

217
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:30,276
- So basically he attempted
suicide ? - Not exactly.

218
00:18:30,327 --> 00:18:34,286
Maybe he just wanted to hurt himself
to attract some attention.

219
00:18:34,327 --> 00:18:36,966
But go now, don't make him
wait, stay close to him.

220
00:18:37,007 --> 00:18:40,443
We'll talk when I'll be back.
Don't think about it. All my best.

221
00:18:40,487 --> 00:18:43,763
You've been very dear. Goodbye.

222
00:18:45,687 --> 00:18:48,076
Mom ?

223
00:18:50,167 --> 00:18:52,920
Here I am. Excuse me, my dear.

224
00:18:56,487 --> 00:19:00,321
- How do you feel ?
- Hm...

225
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:07,717
Don't move.
Please, stay still.

226
00:19:11,967 --> 00:19:15,118
Do you want me to stay here, like this ?

227
00:19:17,887 --> 00:19:21,197
Go in the other room,
I'll stay with the child.

228
00:19:21,247 --> 00:19:23,886
Sit wherever you want.

229
00:19:35,607 --> 00:19:38,075
Happy now ?

230
00:19:39,087 --> 00:19:45,435
Here... Let's stay close
like when you were wee.

231
00:19:45,487 --> 00:19:50,356
Do you remember, during the war
when you came to sleep with me...

232
00:19:50,407 --> 00:19:54,286
..with your frozen feet ?

233
00:19:54,327 --> 00:19:58,286
It felt nice, crouched
under the covers !

234
00:20:02,047 --> 00:20:06,996
Do you remember hearing the sirens ?

235
00:20:07,047 --> 00:20:13,395
You said: ''Bombs'',
and then you fell asleep.

236
00:20:15,327 --> 00:20:19,240
You didn't even realize when we
descended in the basement.

237
00:20:21,847 --> 00:20:25,442
I carried you
all wrapped up in covers !

238
00:20:28,607 --> 00:20:33,123
Do you remember that wonderful sunny
day, in the contryside...

239
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:36,796
..when that soldier was rude to me,
for no reason at all.

240
00:20:36,847 --> 00:20:42,046
- What did you tell him ?
- I don't remember. What did I tell him ?

241
00:20:42,087 --> 00:20:46,399
You stood up like a grown man
and told him:...

242
00:20:46,447 --> 00:20:49,883
...''Do you want me to punch
you on your nose?''.

243
00:20:52,287 --> 00:20:55,120
My man !

244
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:59,796
And do you remember when daddy came
back from war ?

245
00:20:59,847 --> 00:21:05,558
Then you weren't with me anymore.

246
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:14,885
I'll be with you again !
I'm here with you !

247
00:21:14,927 --> 00:21:18,806
- Like when I had my appendix done ?
- Yes !

248
00:21:18,847 --> 00:21:23,284
Yes, like that time,
just like that time !

249
00:21:23,327 --> 00:21:27,240
I'll be forever with you !
Forever and ever and ever !

250
00:22:01,407 --> 00:22:06,765
- Michel did not have an accident.
- What ? What are you saying ?

251
00:22:06,807 --> 00:22:10,686
Michel, I'm saying...

252
00:22:10,727 --> 00:22:15,039
It was no accident. He tried
to kill himself.

253
00:22:15,087 --> 00:22:20,286
Come on dear, stop your imagination.

254
00:22:20,327 --> 00:22:24,320
No, it's true, he tried to kill himself.

255
00:22:24,367 --> 00:22:29,236
It's impossible !
It's absurd, there are no reasons.

256
00:22:30,647 --> 00:22:36,756
- Who said that ?
- The hospital doctor told Andrea.

257
00:22:36,807 --> 00:22:40,482
He's crazy! They're both crazy!

258
00:22:43,327 --> 00:22:46,922
No... no, dear, it's true.

259
00:22:48,407 --> 00:22:51,604
I understood it by myself.

260
00:22:53,487 --> 00:22:58,356
And he told me.
In his way, but he told me.

261
00:22:58,407 --> 00:23:02,241
Oh, George, we should change everything
in our life !

262
00:23:02,287 --> 00:23:06,075
We must !
We can't continue like this !

263
00:23:17,407 --> 00:23:20,717
George ? George !

264
00:23:22,207 --> 00:23:24,243
- What happened ?
- No !

265
00:23:24,287 --> 00:23:27,563
- Let me in ! What happened ?
- You can't get in, it's too late !

266
00:23:27,607 --> 00:23:30,246
- Let me in !
- He's dead !

267
00:23:30,287 --> 00:23:33,677
- He's dead ! He's dead !
- Michel ! Michel !

268
00:23:34,367 --> 00:23:38,360
Quick, Lady's mother want to see what
we have prepared.

269
00:23:38,407 --> 00:23:40,523
Put it here.

270
00:23:40,567 --> 00:23:45,118
I can't take it anymore !
Three sleepless night in a row.

271
00:23:58,047 --> 00:24:00,322
Is it ok, Mrs. ?

272
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:05,319
It's fine, Cesira.
Bring it in.

273
00:24:05,367 --> 00:24:08,916
One cannot survive on
orange juice alone !

274
00:24:12,487 --> 00:24:15,240
I'll go to see her.

275
00:24:22,607 --> 00:24:28,318
- Good evening, dear. How do you feel ?
- Fine enough.

276
00:24:30,047 --> 00:24:32,800
Why didn't you eat anything ?

277
00:24:32,847 --> 00:24:37,875
I didn't feel like. I'll eat later.

278
00:24:37,927 --> 00:24:40,805
You can't go on like this...

279
00:24:40,847 --> 00:24:45,682
..ten days without moving
or even eating !

280
00:24:45,727 --> 00:24:47,797
You need to shake yourself off.

281
00:24:47,847 --> 00:24:51,999
Please, I'm fine.
I'll get better.

282
00:24:52,047 --> 00:24:57,041
Don't want to bore you, but i need to
insist, for your own good.

283
00:24:57,087 --> 00:25:00,966
- Oh, George...
- Please, let me finish.

284
00:25:01,007 --> 00:25:06,127
Even against our will,
we must go on with life.

285
00:25:06,167 --> 00:25:12,481
Life goes on and...
we have to follow it.

286
00:25:14,807 --> 00:25:16,957
Think about your mother.

287
00:25:17,007 --> 00:25:22,684
At her age, she flew in from
America just to see you !

288
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:27,442
And in three days
you almost didn't speak to her.

289
00:25:27,487 --> 00:25:32,277
If you don't want to think about
yourself, think about her, at least.

290
00:25:32,327 --> 00:25:37,003
No, George, I can't.
Try to explain it to her.

291
00:25:39,367 --> 00:25:43,599
I need to stay alone.
I need a lot of rest.

292
00:25:43,647 --> 00:25:46,639
Come in.

293
00:25:51,407 --> 00:25:53,602
It's from London.

294
00:25:55,167 --> 00:25:58,637
Hello ? Hello !

295
00:26:02,527 --> 00:26:06,236
Can you speak louder?
I can't hear.

296
00:26:06,287 --> 00:26:10,917
Ah, yes... Thanks.

297
00:26:11,727 --> 00:26:14,764
Good.
I'll send you a cablegram.

298
00:26:14,807 --> 00:26:17,799
No, call me at the office
tomorrow morning.

299
00:26:17,847 --> 00:26:20,361
Thanks. Goodbye.

300
00:26:22,167 --> 00:26:27,560
Don't worry for me, George,
it will pass, but I need time.

301
00:26:27,607 --> 00:26:31,759
- Why don't you take one of these
sleeping pills ? They might help. - Yes.

302
00:26:31,807 --> 00:26:37,439
- You'd sleep. You need rest
more than anything else - Yes.

303
00:26:37,487 --> 00:26:41,082
Sleep would do more
than any cure.

304
00:26:41,127 --> 00:26:44,756
Yes, yes dear, don't worry,
don't worry, but...

305
00:26:46,007 --> 00:26:48,965
Please, don't leave mom alone.

306
00:26:49,007 --> 00:26:53,319
Go to her, then come back to me
after you've had lunch.

307
00:27:01,047 --> 00:27:05,165
- Should I turn off the lights ?
- Yes, please.

308
00:27:35,287 --> 00:27:40,122
Hello, who is it ?
Oh, Andrea, it's her!

309
00:27:40,167 --> 00:27:43,876
Yes, I called her many times,
I wanted to talk.

310
00:27:43,927 --> 00:27:50,480
Yes... It's urgent.
Won't tonight be fine ?

311
00:27:51,527 --> 00:27:55,759
Ah, excuse me, but it's so
important for me !

312
00:27:55,807 --> 00:27:59,846
No, no, I'm coming to you.

313
00:27:59,887 --> 00:28:04,563
Yes, right now. Where's the newspaper office?

314
00:28:04,607 --> 00:28:08,885
Sure, right now. I'll be there
in a while. Yes.

315
00:28:18,167 --> 00:28:21,603
- Irene dear...
- Did you know ?

316
00:28:21,647 --> 00:28:26,926
- So sudden...
-It was an embolism.

317
00:28:26,967 --> 00:28:30,118
Tell me:
what can I do for you ?

318
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:35,878
Nothing, I'm afraid. Nothing.

319
00:28:35,927 --> 00:28:38,760
- Where are we going ?
- Wherever you want. I don't care.

320
00:28:38,807 --> 00:28:42,766
I don't know. A quiet place,
where we could talk.

321
00:28:42,807 --> 00:28:46,846
Oh, I was anxiously waiting
for your return !

322
00:28:46,887 --> 00:28:49,606
Had I known all the details
beforehand...

323
00:28:49,647 --> 00:28:54,357
- I called the newspaper so many
times ! - They told me.

324
00:28:54,407 --> 00:28:58,241
And now that I can ask you
all the questions,...

325
00:28:58,287 --> 00:29:02,075
..I feel that it's useless.

326
00:29:04,607 --> 00:29:09,601
Irene, don't be like this.
Try to be strong, please.

327
00:29:09,647 --> 00:29:14,880
- At times I don't know what I'm doing.
- I understand you, dear.

328
00:29:14,927 --> 00:29:18,840
- Where are you going now ? Back to the newspaper ?
- No, not yet.

329
00:29:18,887 --> 00:29:22,641
I might stay a bit more with you,
if you wish. Turn left.

330
00:29:22,687 --> 00:29:24,962
I'm not very entertaining.

331
00:29:50,287 --> 00:29:52,357
Why don't we step outside ?

332
00:29:52,407 --> 00:29:55,717
Let's breathe some air
and talk a bit.

333
00:30:11,567 --> 00:30:17,358
- This square is impressing, isn't it ?
- Yes...

334
00:30:19,847 --> 00:30:22,964
Michel must have said rather painful
things, during the anesthesia,...

335
00:30:23,007 --> 00:30:26,795
..to make so that the doctor could
understand it was a voluntary gesture.

336
00:30:26,847 --> 00:30:30,237
Listen to me, Irene,
don't torment yourself.

337
00:30:32,567 --> 00:30:35,320
Ah, Andrea, what a fatality !

338
00:30:35,367 --> 00:30:38,962
If things had gone otherwise !

339
00:30:39,007 --> 00:30:42,397
Had I said a word, made a gesture
rather than another...

340
00:30:42,447 --> 00:30:46,565
Do you understand how atrocious it is
that a word one can't delete...

341
00:30:46,607 --> 00:30:50,998
..resulted in Michel's death ?

342
00:30:51,047 --> 00:30:55,199
I can't take it anymore,
I can't live, I can't !

343
00:30:55,247 --> 00:30:59,798
Irene, torment is useless.

344
00:30:59,847 --> 00:31:03,237
Useless to repeat: ''Had I said...
Had I done...'' ?

345
00:31:03,287 --> 00:31:05,517
Things are what they are.

346
00:31:05,567 --> 00:31:09,719
It was destiny, then.
Why such a destiny ?

347
00:31:09,767 --> 00:31:13,601
I never mentioned
destiny. What destiny ?

348
00:31:13,647 --> 00:31:16,286
Then, if it isn't destiny,
I'm the one to blame.

349
00:31:16,327 --> 00:31:19,080
No, Irene, it's not your fault.

350
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:23,245
Blame society, as it allows
such horrors to happen.

351
00:31:23,287 --> 00:31:25,562
What's society role in this ?

352
00:31:25,607 --> 00:31:31,364
A children whose first impressions
of the world around him...

353
00:31:31,407 --> 00:31:35,195
..were fear, bombings, war...

354
00:31:35,247 --> 00:31:38,045
Who's to blame ?

355
00:31:38,087 --> 00:31:41,762
Why should children be the ones who pay ?

356
00:31:41,807 --> 00:31:45,004
It isn't right.
Then, God isn't right.

357
00:31:45,047 --> 00:31:48,084
Think about this:
maybe a children must die...

358
00:31:48,127 --> 00:31:52,086
..because parents can't afford
the needed medicine.

359
00:31:52,127 --> 00:31:56,200
It happened today,
at the newspaper:...

360
00:31:56,247 --> 00:32:01,196
..a mother came to beg us to do
something to help her.

361
00:32:01,247 --> 00:32:05,684
She has four childs, her husband
is a miser and cleans the streets,...

362
00:32:05,727 --> 00:32:08,287
..he earns just about enough
to buy food.

363
00:32:08,327 --> 00:32:12,798
The medicine costs so much, it's
a new product, made in America.

364
00:32:12,847 --> 00:32:15,645
Is it possible for the child's life
to be bound...

365
00:32:15,687 --> 00:32:18,599
..to the money quantity needed
to buy the medicine ?

366
00:32:18,647 --> 00:32:22,162
Why didn't you tell me earlier ?
I can provide the needed amount.

367
00:32:22,207 --> 00:32:24,846
How could we do it ?
We can go there right now.

368
00:32:24,887 --> 00:32:27,799
- No, tomorrow will be ok.
- Yes...

369
00:32:27,847 --> 00:32:32,045
- We'll go there together, eh ?
- Sure.

370
00:32:53,027 --> 00:32:58,101
- Oh, George...
- Where the hell have you been ?

371
00:32:58,147 --> 00:33:01,935
Sorry, but I had to go out.
Didn't the doorman tell you ?

372
00:33:01,587 --> 00:33:04,897
Yes, he told me, but you didn't
have to go out like this.

373
00:33:04,947 --> 00:33:09,975
I've spent the last hours walking from the
door to the window like a wolf in a cage.

374
00:33:10,027 --> 00:33:12,541
Why didn't you tell me you were going out ?

375
00:33:12,587 --> 00:33:17,456
I was afraid horrible things
happened to you.

376
00:33:17,507 --> 00:33:24,504
- Do you understand that my nervous
condition... - You're right, I'm sorry.

377
00:33:24,547 --> 00:33:28,222
You must be patient with me.

378
00:33:28,267 --> 00:33:33,295
At times... I think I'm going crazy.

379
00:33:33,347 --> 00:33:37,545
- Can you at least tell me where you've been ?
- I've been with Andrea.

380
00:33:37,587 --> 00:33:43,025
- Andrea ? What did you wanted from him ?
- I don't know what I'm doing.

381
00:33:50,187 --> 00:33:53,497
I'm unable to explain it, even
to myself.

382
00:33:57,027 --> 00:34:02,021
Irene, you must find the strength...
to keep on living.

383
00:34:06,107 --> 00:34:09,338
We are despaired,
let's try to help each other.

384
00:34:09,387 --> 00:34:14,256
It will pass, don't worry.
We'll find a way out.

385
00:34:16,947 --> 00:34:20,781
We'll find a way out...
together.

386
00:34:23,867 --> 00:34:28,657
Nobody could help you,
not even Andrea.

387
00:34:28,707 --> 00:34:32,586
You need me
exactly as I need you.

388
00:34:32,627 --> 00:34:36,859
Yes, George, everything will be fine.

389
00:34:53,747 --> 00:34:59,617
- Excuse me, Where's the third lot ?
- Over there. Come, I'll escort you.

390
00:35:03,107 --> 00:35:05,462
- There it is.
- Thank you.

391
00:35:20,947 --> 00:35:23,017
Here we are.

392
00:35:38,907 --> 00:35:41,819
- Does Galli family live here?
- Please, get in.

393
00:35:41,867 --> 00:35:44,939
I escorted them here.

394
00:35:44,987 --> 00:35:48,502
- Please.
- Galli, there's someone for you.

395
00:35:48,547 --> 00:35:51,778
- May I ?
- Is it you, Sir ? Good morning !

396
00:35:51,827 --> 00:35:55,661
- I brought that stuff.
- Oh, Jesus, thank you ! - Here.

397
00:35:55,707 --> 00:35:59,017
This will be enough for both medicines
and hospital expenses.

398
00:35:59,067 --> 00:36:02,537
If you'll need something else in the future,
we'll try to help.

399
00:36:02,587 --> 00:36:07,581
Thanks.
Do you see the state we live in ?

400
00:36:07,627 --> 00:36:13,020
We are sub-renting
this room. We are six.

401
00:36:13,067 --> 00:36:16,980
Without Bruno, the house feels empty.

402
00:36:18,827 --> 00:36:22,820
- Well, goodbye. Best wishes.
- Goodbye. Thank you.

403
00:36:22,867 --> 00:36:26,542
- Thanks so much.
- Youre' welcome. Have a nice day. - You too.

404
00:36:27,787 --> 00:36:32,815
- Is there anyhting for me ? - Yes, doctor,
there's a letter for you. - Thanks.

405
00:36:34,267 --> 00:36:37,145
Ah, I was looking for you.

406
00:36:37,187 --> 00:36:40,338
- Mister Pisani,
Mrs. Gerard. - How do you do.

407
00:36:40,387 --> 00:36:44,221
- How should I write it?
- I'll think about it. Wait.

408
00:36:44,267 --> 00:36:46,542
Please.

409
00:36:48,187 --> 00:36:50,655
Sit down, Irene.

410
00:36:50,707 --> 00:36:56,976
So... This must go.
This one, even.

411
00:36:57,027 --> 00:37:01,464
Write : ''The state department
initiative...''

412
00:37:01,507 --> 00:37:04,419
''..must be put in relation...''

413
00:37:04,467 --> 00:37:08,745
''..with the clear attempt
of american financiary entities...''

414
00:37:08,787 --> 00:37:15,101
''..to surpass England
and appropriate Persian oils.''

415
00:37:15,147 --> 00:37:20,619
''The english government follows
the U.S. Initiative...''

416
00:37:20,667 --> 00:37:24,421
''..with extreme diffidence.''

417
00:37:25,867 --> 00:37:28,222
And how should I title it?

418
00:37:28,267 --> 00:37:32,260
Write: ''Panic among London finances...''

419
00:37:32,307 --> 00:37:34,696
''..for the new U.S. Persian manoeuvre.''

420
00:37:34,747 --> 00:37:38,296
- Over two columns ? - No, over three,
in the first page.

421
00:37:38,347 --> 00:37:41,020
- Well. Good morning, lady.
- Good morning.

422
00:37:41,067 --> 00:37:45,026
- Can you wait a bit ?
- It's better for me to go, I'm tired.

423
00:37:45,067 --> 00:37:49,140
- I'm sorry that you have to go on your own.
- Don't worry.

424
00:37:49,187 --> 00:37:55,183
Irene, listen to me: don't close yourself
shut in your own pain.

425
00:37:55,227 --> 00:37:57,422
Yes.

426
00:37:58,627 --> 00:38:03,985
I was thinking: it's strange how
that people seems resigned.

427
00:38:04,027 --> 00:38:08,737
It is our duty to wake them up,
shake them up, give them a conscience.

428
00:38:08,787 --> 00:38:12,575
- Or just give them hope. - A conscience,
a conscience. We must help them.

429
00:38:12,627 --> 00:38:18,065
- Yes, we must help them.
- Beside us they might learn many things.

430
00:38:18,107 --> 00:38:23,784
- Take it. Are you interested ?
It's a good book. - Thanks.

431
00:38:23,827 --> 00:38:27,024
Let's have a coffee.

432
00:38:38,707 --> 00:38:41,779
- Mister Casati is calling.
- Ah, Yes.

433
00:38:41,827 --> 00:38:44,864
Mom, can you do it, please?

434
00:38:46,667 --> 00:38:52,503
Yes ? Ah, the baby
is back home? Is he fine ?

435
00:38:52,547 --> 00:38:57,667
Thanks, Andrea. No, don't worry.
I'll go there if you can't.

436
00:38:57,707 --> 00:39:00,460
Sure, I remember which
bus I should take.

437
00:39:00,507 --> 00:39:04,216
I'm going today.
Thanks, Andrea. Goodbye.

438
00:39:09,707 --> 00:39:14,144
- You're happy, eh ?
- Yes, it's good news.

439
00:39:14,187 --> 00:39:20,456
Tell me, Irene: I saw some books,
some magazines around...

440
00:39:20,507 --> 00:39:24,739
- What are you planning?
- I'm doing nothing wrong, mom.

441
00:39:24,787 --> 00:39:28,541
Listen to me... Give me the knit job.

442
00:39:30,387 --> 00:39:34,426
Do you know that in the States
they arrested all communists ?

443
00:39:34,467 --> 00:39:37,937
I understand,
after what happened to you...

444
00:39:37,987 --> 00:39:41,457
But to get to the point to
forget who you are...

445
00:39:41,507 --> 00:39:44,943
Do you want to end up in a
concentration camp, in case of war ?

446
00:39:44,987 --> 00:39:47,785
Listen to me:
come with me in England.

447
00:39:47,827 --> 00:39:50,341
- Mom, please...
- What's this got to do with anything?

448
00:39:50,387 --> 00:39:54,266
Listen to me, you who might, mom.
I know what my duties are.

449
00:39:54,307 --> 00:39:58,778
But, see, I'm looking for something...
Don't you understand ?

450
00:40:02,107 --> 00:40:04,382
Well.

451
00:40:06,627 --> 00:40:11,382
Why don't you tell exactly what
you think ? That I've gone crazy !

452
00:40:17,987 --> 00:40:21,616
Don't talk to her like that.
Irene is an intelligent woman.

453
00:40:21,667 --> 00:40:24,864
We can't stop her,
we have to meet her halfawy,...

454
00:40:24,907 --> 00:40:28,377
..wrap her in warmness and care,
as if she was sick and recovering.

455
